Cerebral palsy (CP) is a group of permanent movement disorders that appear in early childhood. Signs and symptoms vary among people and over time. Things behave a bit differently aboard the International Space Station.

Sure, floating looks fun, but microgravity could also unlock new scientific discoveries.
 
Microgravity makes the station the perfect place to perform research that is changing the lives of people on Earth and preparing us to go deeper into space.

Come along with us as we follow a team of scientists as they launch their research off our planet and to the space station to see what microgravity may reveal.

Stay tuned for future episodes dropping every Friday and Monday leading up to the 20th anniversary of continuous human presence on the International Space Station on Nov. 2, 2020. #SpaceStation20th
